27 COMMUNICATION AND CUSTOMER SERVICES
28 Sec. 240. (1) In addition to supporting the existing
29 archeological responsibilities of the department within the
WAM S06115'26 (S-1) xtbwoc

27
1 Michigan History Center, the funds appropriated in part 1 for
2 cultural resource management and cultural resource management one-
3 time must be utilized to establish an ongoing process of increased
4 consultation with known lineal descendants and officials of Native
5 American tribes on whose aboriginal lands a planned archeological
6 activity will occur or an inadvertent discovery has been made. The
7 consultation must address the identification, treatment, and
8 disposition of Native American cultural items.
9 (2) The department is encouraged to, whenever possible,
10 repatriate or transfer from its collections Native American
11 cultural items, including human remains, funerary objects, sacred
12 objects, and objects of cultural patrimony, to the lineal
13 descendants and to Native American tribes described in subsection
14 (1).
