1 Sec. 257. The department shall prioritize right-of-way permits
2 or easements for construction or maintenance of broadband
3 facilities on state land and shall not require a centerline survey
4 as a condition of the road right-of-way permit or easement if the
5 applicant can provide detailed engineering plans and if the
6 broadband facilities are contained completely in the right-of-way.
7 If the broadband provider secures a road right-of-way permit to
8 construct or maintain broadband facilities required by the
9 municipal, county, or state entity that owns or controls the public
10 road, the department shall not require the broadband provider to
11 obtain a permit or easement if the broadband facility is contained
12 completely within the road right-of-way. If installation of
13 broadband facilities cannot be contained completely within the
14 right-of-way and requires placement of the infrastructure on public
15 lands, an easement will be required, and a certified survey may be
16 required. If installation of broadband facilities being placed in
17 the road right-of-way requires utilization of public lands, a
18 permit may be required.
19
