24 ONE-TIME APPROPRIATIONS
25 Sec. 1201. (1) Funds appropriated in part 1 for whitefish
26 recovery must be used by the department to support efforts to
27 recover and monitor not more than 3 lake whitefish stocks.
28 (2) Funds appropriated under this section must be used for
29 activities that include, but are not limited to, spawning and
WAM S06115'26 (S-1) xtbwoc

32
1 rearing activities and post-stocking assessment and evaluation
2 necessary to support lake whitefish stock recovery.
3 (3) The department may contract with or enter into agreements
4 with qualified nonprofit, research-based organizations to implement
5 a lake whitefish stock recovery plan developed by the department.
6 (4) Activities under this section must be conducted using
7 department-owned hatchery facilities or facilities owned or
8 operated by partners contracted under subsection (3).
9 (5) Funds appropriated under this section must not be used for
10 operational expenses or for the support of full-time equated
11 positions or permanent state positions. The department may utilize
12 limited-term employees as necessary to carry out the purposes of
13 this section.
